</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[136,1452,1922,2093]" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1958,1984]" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poeppig &amp; Endlicher" authorityYear="1865" box="[294,579,1958,1984]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monophyllus">
<emphasis box="[294,579,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Myoxanthus monophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by its multiple congested flowers with long narrow sepals and petals and pubescent floral bract covering the pedicel, ovary and base of the perianth. 
<bibRefCitation author="Christenson, E. A." box="[1101,1317,1994,2021]" pageId="30" pageNumber="241" pagination="31 - 43" refId="ref27936" refString="Christenson, E. A. (1995) Type specimens of Orchidaceae conserved at the Komarov Institute, St. Petersburg, Russia (LE). Brittonia 47: 31 - 43. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2807246" type="journal article" year="1995">Christenson (1995)</bibRefCitation>
reported an isotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poeppig &amp; Endlicher" authorityYear="1865" box="[255,436,2030,2056]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monophyllus">
<emphasis box="[255,436,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">M. monophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at LE, which we have not seen. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1983" box="[805,1029,2030,2056]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gorgon">
<emphasis box="[805,1029,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Myoxanthus gorgon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar but with a shorter, reflexed perianth (see comments under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1983" box="[482,599,2067,2092]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gorgon">
<emphasis box="[482,599,2067,2092]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">M. gorgon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for a comparison). 
<taxonomicName authority="Lindl." authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1836" box="[821,1155,2066,2092]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poeppigii">
<emphasis box="[821,1080,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">Pleurothallis poeppigii</emphasis>
Lindl.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Schltr." authorityName="Schlechter" authorityYear="1921" box="[1210,1452,2066,2092]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="30" pageNumber="241" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myoxanthus">
<emphasis box="[1210,1372,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="241">P. myoxanthus</emphasis>
Schltr.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1451,158,221]" pageId="31" pageNumber="242">
are replacement names based on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poeppig &amp; Endlicher" authorityYear="1865" box="[520,704,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="242" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monophyllus">
<emphasis box="[520,704,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="242">M. monophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as clearly stated by their respective authors. The two names are therefore homotypic synonyms, the latter superfluous.
</paragraph>
